        "timeoriginalestimate": null,
        "description": "We collapse contiguous Uint8Arrays that share the same underlying ArrayBuffer and have overlapping byte ranges. This was done to maintain true zero-copy behavior when using certain node core streams that use a buffer pool internally, and could write chunks of the same logical Arrow Message at out-of-order byte offsets in the pool.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately this can also lead to a bug where, in rare cases, buffers are swapped while writing Arrow Messages too. We could have a flag to indicate whether we think collapsing out-of-order same-buffer chunks is safe, but I'm not sure if we can always know that, so\u00a0I'd prefer\u00a0to take it out and incur the copy cost.",
